A shootout between suspects and cops left one suspect dead and
eight suspects arrested in Boksburg. This was after a joint team that comprises of Tactical Operations
Management Section (TOMS) of the Hawks at Head Office, Crime Intelligence,
Gauteng Traffic Police's Saturation Unit, Tracker Connect and Badboyz Security
swiftly responded to intelligence information received about armed suspects
planning to commit a truck hijacking. Police spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Philani Nkwalase said, “On the
22 July 2022, the crime intelligence-led information was operationalised to
intercept the suspects and the vehicles fitting the description was spotted on
R554 in Boksburg following an eight-ton truck. The police were greeted with
gunfire when they attempted to stop the suspects.” Mkwalase added, “A shoot-out ensued as the police returned fire.
One of nine suspects was fatally wounded, four others were wounded and taken to
hospital whilst the remaining four were immediately arrested. “Two vehicles allegedly used in the commission of the crime and
three illegal firearms found in both vehicles were seized.” READ: SHOOTOUT leave one suspect dead and three arrested! Mkwalase said eight suspects between the ages of 26 and 48 are
expected to appear in the Boksburg Magistrates court soon to face multiple
charges that include murder, attempted murder, illegal possession of firearm
and ammunition as well as conspiracy to commit a crime.